{"title":"Updated Marin Four Corners is Ready for “Utilitour” Adventure Touring w/ New Geo, Frame Mounts & More!","link":"https://bikerumor.com/updated-marin-four-corners-adventure-touring-bike/","date":1705675792000,"content":"<p><img width=\"1280\" height=\"853\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-hero-outside.jpeg\" alt=\"Marin Four Corners 1 hero outside\" loading=\"lazy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-hero-outside.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-hero-outside-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-hero-outside-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-hero-outside-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-hero-outside-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-hero-outside-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></p>\n<p>Straight outta Petaluma, California, comes the news that Marin Bikes is releasing an updated version of the popular Four Corners adventure touring bike with the Four Corners 1. For decades, the Four Corners has been a staple in Marin’s drop bar line. The model was reinvented in 2016 in celebration of Marin Bikes’ 30th anniversary. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-side-outside.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-side-outside-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Marin Four Corners 1 side outside\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-side-outside-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-side-outside-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-side-outside-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-side-outside-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-side-outside-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-side-outside.jpeg 1280w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photo/Marin Bikes)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Marin calls these stout, steel rigs “Ultilituor” adventure touring bicycles. And they have been used for everything from your average weekday commute to transcontinental excursions. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-logo.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-logo-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Marin Four Corners 1 logo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-logo-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-logo-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-logo-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-logo-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-logo-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-logo.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Since 2018 the Four Corners model has used size-specific wheel sizes (XSmall &amp; Small = 650b, and Medium, Large, and XLarge = 700c) to help with proper rider fit, and a more balanced riding experience. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-upright-wilderness.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-upright-wilderness-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Marin Four Corners 1 upright wilderness\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-upright-wilderness-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-upright-wilderness-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-upright-wilderness-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-upright-wilderness-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-upright-wilderness-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-upright-wilderness.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Taller head tubes and a high stack keep the riding position more upright for better sightseeing, better comfort, and better visibility. More frame-carrying capacity allows for a bigger frame bag to be used.</p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Updates for the Four Corners 1 </h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Marin has adjusted the geometry on the Four Corners 1 a little. Because the headtube has a 5° slacker angle and is 10mm shorter, they were able to keep the stack height virtually untouched. The updated seat tubes are now dropper post-compatible. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-handlebar-width.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-handlebar-width-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Marin Four Corners 1 handlebar width\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-handlebar-width-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-handlebar-width-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-handlebar-width-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-handlebar-width-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-handlebar-width-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-handlebar-width.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Hoping to give riders more real estate for handlebar bags the updated handlebars are wider at 400-440mm. Therefore, with the new widths, riders will find a more stable stance while off-road. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-packed-down.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-packed-down-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Marin Four Corners 1 packed down\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-packed-down-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-packed-down-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-packed-down-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-packed-down-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-packed-down-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-packed-down.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The number of accessory mounts on the frame has increased as well, with two on the top of the top tube near the head tube and three on the underside of the down tube. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-with-cabin.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-with-cabin-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Marin Four Corners 1 with cabin\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-with-cabin-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-with-cabin-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-with-cabin-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-with-cabin-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-with-cabin-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-with-cabin.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Get a custom frame bag made for your FourCorners with a multitude of mounts inside the frame. There will be a detailed “map” of these on Marin’s website. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-close-up-technical-terrain.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"558\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-close-up-technical-terrain-800x558.jpeg\" alt=\"Marin Four Corners 1 close up technical terrain\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-close-up-technical-terrain-800x558.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-close-up-technical-terrain-297x207.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-close-up-technical-terrain-120x84.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-close-up-technical-terrain-768x535.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-close-up-technical-terrain.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s talk tire clearance. With the new updated Four Corners 1 comes 40mm tires on both wheel sizes and has clearance to fit up to 45mm tires on both wheel sizes. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-drivetrain.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-drivetrain-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Marin Four Corners 1 drivetrain\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-drivetrain-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-drivetrain-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-drivetrain-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-drivetrain-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-drivetrain-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-drivetrain.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-brakes.jpeg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-brakes-800x533.jpeg\" alt=\"Marin Four Corners 1 brakes\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-brakes-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-brakes-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-brakes-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-brakes-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-brakes-720x480.jpeg 720w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Marin-Four-Corners-1-brakes.jpeg 1280w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The drive train for the Four Corners 1 is spec’d with Shimano’s great, wide-range, traditional, and dependable Sora 3×9. The stopping power is provided by the capable TRP Spyre-C cable-actuated disc brakes. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Geometry Chart</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/pavement-geo-e1705599370317.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"365\" height=\"306\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/pavement-geo-e1705599370317.png\" alt=\"Marin Four Corners 1 Geo Chart\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/pavement-geo-e1705599370317.png 365w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/pavement-geo-e1705599370317-297x249.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/pavement-geo-e1705599370317-120x101.png 120w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/4C1-geos.png\"><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"442\" height=\"724\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/4C1-geos.png\" alt=\"Marin Four Corners 1 Geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/4C1-geos.png 442w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/4C1-geos-183x300.png 183w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/4C1-geos-73x120.png 73w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Features and Retail</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Retail: $999</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sizes: X-Small, Small, Medium, Large, X-Large</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Colors: Blue or Black</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Series 1 butted CroMo frame and fork </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Size-specific wheel sizes (XS &amp; S = 650b, M, L, XL = 700c)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shimano Sora 3×9 drivetrain</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tektro Spyre-C road mechanical disc brakes</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Vee Tire Co GP Vee 40mm tires</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.marinbikes.com/\" target=\"_blank\">MarinBikes.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/updated-marin-four-corners-adventure-touring-bike/\">Updated Marin Four Corners is Ready for “Utilitour” Adventure Touring w/ New Geo, Frame Mounts &amp; More!</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"6172c789141bad038aea90537f5a4c6278a99343cee9916f198f86a82ac3ec2e","category":"Cycling"}